 &quot;sorry I can't group with you, your god sucks and I'm a roleplayer..... don't mind me sitting here by myself while you pointlessly hack and re-hack those MOBs....I'm ROLEPLAYING&quot;... yes, yes roleplaying.&quot;<br>
<br>
IMO the ONLY real way to roleplay in a mmorg is to have a pvp element.</font><p><P><i></i></TD><TD valign=top align=LEFT ><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333333>9/24/00</FONT>  <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333333>5:14:47 pm</FONT><BR></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#dcdeed><TD ALIGN=LEFT width=80% valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"><B>Re: roleplaying in nameless</B></FONT></TD><TD ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"><A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ujeppocurefinger.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jeppo Curefinger</A></B></FONT></FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">The roleplay element that occurs in the chat channels is rather sad on occassion.  The /ooc's that insult people trying to roleplay are silly and should be ignored.  What I usually do is if I am running through Nektulos Forest with my Halfling Cleric is /shout &quot;Insult Dark Elves here&quot;.  This, in turn, gets me a few STFU's or whatever, but there is always at least one person that knows whats up and will /shout &quot;Jeppo, your kind isn't wanted here type response&quot;.  <br>
<br>
As soon as I see that one message or two, I take the roleplay to private tells.  Much more fun, and I don't have to read all the /ooc, /shout garbage while I roleplay with someone interesting.  Roleplaying is not hard if you just adapt to the situation that the chat system gives you.<br>
